.START 

Helene Curtis Industries Inc. said earnings for the fiscal second quarter ended Aug. 31 jumped 33% to $6.6 million, or 71 cents a share, in part because of strengthening sales of shampoo and hair conditioner products. 

In the year-earlier quarter, the beauty and hair-care products maker earned $5 million, or 65 cents a share.
Sales rose 27% to $199 million from $157.2 million. 

The company said its Salon Selectives line was one of the fastest growing brands in the industry in the quarter. 

First-half earnings rose 34% to $8.8 million, or 95 cents a share, from $6.6 million, or 87 cents a share.
Sales increased 22% to $359.2 million from $295 million. 

Per share earnings are adjusted for a 2-for-1 stock split paid Aug. 1. 

